      "writtenOn": "2020-07-14T20:48:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I started to do this, and quickly realized that I had forgotten something very basic: texture effect *does* use (modulate by) the input color. Image shader has a slightly different behavior (it only scales by paint alpha), but it was enough to realize that even my first test case wasn\u0027t doing what I thought. I fixed that test case, but...\n\nThis means that if we want to change the default inputColor for invokeChild, we\u0027d need to explicitly pass \"half4(1)\" every time we want to sample a child and *not* get the implicit modulation from a texture effect.",
      "parentUuid": "9f3eb1f6_7a969dcd",
